      "rationale": "Linear-elastic titanium alloy constitutive model is well-established for pre-yield regime. Bilinear isotropic hardening used post-yield with parameters derived from coupon testing. Contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Model form uncertainty is a recognized contributor to the wide uncertainty bounds on yield force (explicitly documented in vr-yieldforce); this is accepted as residual risk. Gradation 2 achieved through documented model form uncertainty quantification and sensitivity studies."
